cabulary to think about what it means to be human in this new age of consumption-produced waste, and reflects on what rubbish allows us to learn about our relationship with the natural world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aConsumption (Economics)xSocial aspects. 0aRefuse and refuse disposalxSocial aspects. 4aCommunication : Communication. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Postcolonial Studies. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Philosophy. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Politics. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2020z978311149149340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848019040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438480190423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438480190/original  a978-3-11-149149-3  SUNY Press eBook Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles